File: AP Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - Kenyan police officials say three police officers were killed and seven others wounded as gunmen suspected to be al-Shabaab militants attacked Pandaguo center, Lamu County.Two officials, who insisted on anonymity because they are not authorized to speak with the press, said on Wednesday it took a seven-hour gun battle for the military and police to retake the village center.Police spokesperson George Kinoti confirmed the death toll.Officials said about 100 militants attacked the village and burned the local police post, a primary school and a dispensary. Al-Shabaab has vowed revenge for Kenya's 2011 deployment of troops to Somalia to fight the group. Al-Shabaab has carried out more than 100 attacks in Kenya.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.